From: Sven Schnelle <svens@linux.ibm.com>
Date: Thu, 29 Feb 2024 08:34:43 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] s390/stp: Default to enabled
Git-commit: b1052a917362d0776d272e6446ce2dc78b75342d
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
References: jsc#PED-15168

With time steering moved to userspace, stp can be enabled
by default.

Signed-off-by: Sven Schnelle <svens@linux.ibm.com>
Acked-by: Heiko Carstens <hca@linux.ibm.com>
Signed-off-by: Alexander Gordeev <agordeev@linux.ibm.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.com>
---
 arch/s390/kernel/time.c | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/s390/kernel/time.c b/arch/s390/kernel/time.c
index 5a021b6dbb3a..63517b85f4c9 100644
--- a/arch/s390/kernel/time.c
+++ b/arch/s390/kernel/time.c
@@ -397,7 +397,7 @@ struct clock_sync_data {
 /*
  * Server Time Protocol (STP) code.
  */
-static bool stp_online;
+static bool stp_online = true;
 static struct stp_sstpi stp_info;
 static void *stp_page;
 
@@ -423,7 +423,6 @@ static void __init stp_reset(void)
 	if (rc == 0)
 		set_bit(CLOCK_SYNC_HAS_STP, &clock_sync_flags);
 	else if (stp_online) {
-		pr_warn("The real or virtual hardware system does not provide an STP interface\n");
 		free_page((unsigned long) stp_page);
 		stp_page = NULL;
 		stp_online = false;
-- 
2.43.0

